Other packages included in the release:

The aggregate Civet release includes the following packages: mincbet 
(copyright: Alan C. Evans, Claude Lepage, Andrew Janke) & mni_surfreg 
(copyright: Alan C. Evans, Oliver Lyttelton, Steve Robbins, Maxime 
Boucher), which are released under the terms of the GPLv2.0 licence 
(http://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html). Mincbet is a 
minc adaptation of FSL bet version 1.0 by Stephen Smith (University of
Oxford).
The aggregate Civet release also includes the following packages: 
oobicpl (copyright: Alan C. Evans, Jason Lerch, Steve Robbins) and 
laplacian_thickness (copyright: Alan C. Evans, Jason Lerch) which are 
released under the LGPLv2.1 licence 
(https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.1.html).

The aggregate Civet release also includes the following external 
packages, which are available under different licences: Netcdf (v3.6.1),
Hdf5 (v1.8.8), Netpbm (v10.35.94), PCRE (v7.8), Boost (v1.64.0), 
PCRE++ (v0.9.5), CGAL (v3.3.1), GSL (v1.8), and data models. 
Licences for each package are indicated with the release and a summary 
of the licensing information is provided below:

